      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The PoDP consists of a six-section form for easy and quick input of data (Fig. 1). The metadata is organized in projects that can consist of multiple related experiments, identified by their MassIVE accession or MetaboLights study identifier... To enable machine readability of the data, ontologies are used to standardize response options wherever possible.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes the PoDP platform accepting paired omics data with structured metadata requirements and validation via ontologies and standardized fields, but does not explicitly mention JSON schema validation, ajv library, or formal error-report generation as implementation details. The paper focuses on the platform's data structure and metadata requirements conceptually, not the technical validation mechanism.",
