    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/error-report-generation/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The PoDP consists of a six-section form for easy and quick input of data (Fig. 1). The metadata is organized in projects that can consist of multiple related experiments, identified by their MassIVE accession or MetaboLights study identifier. The (meta)genomes(s) used in these experiments can all be added to the same project via a public database identifier... Minimal metadata with information about sample preparation and data collection are recorded in a modular way... To create a BGC\u2013MS/MS link, a MIBiG identifier for the same or similar BGC can be linked with a MS/MS URL and scan number of a single measured molecule or molecular network nodes.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper explicitly describes the PoDP's structured data entry requirements for paired omics projects, including mandatory fields (genome, MS/MS data, sample preparation, extraction method, instrumentation method), which aligns with the scope description.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41589-020-00724-z",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "error-report-generation",
