    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/external-registry-querying/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The PoDP consists of a six-section form for easy and quick input of data (Fig. 1). The metadata is organized in projects that can consist of multiple related experiments, identified by their MassIVE accession or MetaboLights study identifier. The (meta)genomes(s) used in these experiments can all be added to the same project via a public database identifier (e.g., a NCBI GenBank accession number or JGI Genome ID)",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes storing genome identifiers (GenBank, JGI) in project metadata but does NOT describe querying external registries to auto-populate organism names or taxonomic metadata. The PoDP stores identifiers and links to public databases but does not perform the enrichment/injection workflow claimed. The paper states 'The PoDP does not store any metabolomics or genomics datasets, but captures metadata defining pairs of omics datasets in existing public databases' \u2014 it is a linking platform, not an enrichment pipeline.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41589-020-00724-z",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "external-registry-querying",
