    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/json-validation-and-formatting/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Here we introduce the Paired Omics Data Platform (PoDP) to streamline access to paired omics data so that both humans and computers can access and read paired datasets and can also record and exploit validated links between BGCs and metabolites (https://pairedomicsdata.bioinformatics.nl/). In addition to linking these omics data types, the platform stores essential metadata (i.e., growth media, extraction solvent, and ionization mode) using existing ontology where available, thus facilitating reuse of for-the-user relevant sections of paired data.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms that PoDP (paired-data-form repository) stores and organizes metadata and links, but does not explicitly mention JSON schema files (app/public/schema.json), programmatic validation, or Elasticsearch indexing. The paper describes the platform's data storage and metadata organization but not the technical implementation details of JSON schema validation.",
